social_posts.post_text: For my Tuscan wine lovers, introducing the newest vintage of Rosso di Montalcino from iconic producer, Fattoria la Magia ( lamagia ). The deep-rooted estate has been crafting gorgeous Sangiovese from 12-18 year old vineyards that sit over 400 meters above sea level. These are the same grapes used for their Brunello! Notes of ripe fig, tomato and oregano arise on the nose before finishing long with just a hint of wood from their third used casks. Lively and approachable, this medium-bodied wine is perfect for your holiday table this year. #lamagiamontalcino #ad

Havana will always have two loving parents that would do anything in the world for her. Being said, Anthony and I have decided to part ways as a couple. We're cool and remaining friends, business partners and co-parents. Thanks for your respect and support.

Got your xmas morning cocktail covered 🎄 
1/2 oz @massenez_officiel Crème de Griotte Cherry Liqueur
5 oz chilled @dopffetirion Crémant d'Alsace Rosé Brut
Garnish with a cherry if u so desire. Welcome Xo
Just sippin' around, waiting for some snow ... 💭🏂
Not sure what kind of place I think I'm running here.. Got something to trade? 😋 Check my story today for @nomwah 's super easy (but lots of dicing) Vegetarian Dumplings 🥟
New merch at the Sais ✨ @ok_saisonnier

A traditional, skin-contact (four days) style of Pinot Gris from San Luis Obispo. These vines were planted in 2001 at Terah's Bassi Vineyard, just 3 miles from the SLO Bay. This vineyard features loamy sand soils and marine sandstone that offer oceanic minerality. You’ll also find notes of cardamom, smoke, and blood orange. $39 from @kinderhookbottleshop (make sure you're following them for all my silly yet educational wine descriptions like these... from Ramato to Frapatto 😅 wow, sorry guys).
Weekend Starts Now 🍷

I just bought myself flowerrrrs 🌹
Meet the bold and unique VDR (Very Deep Red) by @verydarkredwines , it's a Petite Sirah and Petit Verdot blend (not generally considered complementary partners). These grapes, when grown right, offer ideal sugar-to-acid ratios, voluptuous red fruit, high tannin, intense color, with lavender, mocha, and pomegranate notes on the palate. Pairs perfectly with a great book like @jayshetty 's new, 8 Rules of Love, a revelatory guide to every stage of romance from a former monk (and #1 on Amazon this week)!
Hey singles, at least we don't have to share the bottle, right? 😜
Gettin Golden 💛
Sippin @la_spinetta on this 80 degree last day in PR. Gonna miss ya 🇵🇷
Board Babes 🥽

Storm Sipper ❣️ 100% estate-grown Nero d'Avola from Sicily, this rosso has notes of plum jam, capers, tree bark and cocoa dust. Medium in body and tannin.  Stainless aged only. Pick yours up at @kinderhookbottleshop for $17
One from last night's blind tasting 🥂 I loved how competitive this 80+ person law firm was.. such a blast. Book me for your next corporate or private event 😘 DM or send an email (link in bio)

From one of Alsace's most epic producers, Albert Mann. This Cremant is unlike any other. Zipping with acidity and just-ripe stone fruit, you might also find chalky minerality and freshly baked biscuits on the finish. Got mine at @kinderhookbottleshop
Eating my way through Miami.. favorite restaurants?

A trés abordable (very affordable) Pinot Noir from Pays d'Oc in Southern France. @winebow brings in this full bodied beauty by @fatbastard_wines with notes of crushed strawberry, wild raspberry and dried marjoram. Just $14 retail, folks!

Easily the best under $25 white wine I've had in years. I'd call Hermann Ludes' killer  Riesling an "old Mosel" style: austere, crystalline and largely mineral-and-earth driven. Flint forward and slatey with a smidge of dandelion before the long, massively acidic finish. Excited to taste the rest of your lineup, @weinguthermannludes ❕got mine at @kinderhookbottleshop

If you don't already know, my services include: wine education (staff training for bars and restaurants), wine list curation (menu upgrade), and events (private and public wine classes) so hit me up/tell your friends. I am currently accepting new clients from Rhinebeck to Saratoga! Let's up your wine game 😚

Another day, another rosé 💕

Two Hillarys always make a right 👯
Happy to be her mama 🤍 'fit by @oeufnyc (in true IG fashion 😅)
One from the weekend 🌷 hope all my mamas did something relaxing

From Paso Robles, @ancientpeaks Sauvignon Blanc is showing notes of grapefruit, peach, papaya and citrus on the nose and palate. The bright, tangy finish makes this wine a perfect match for summer favs like steamed clams, crab cakes and chicken kabobs. Delicious!

One of my favorite stops today, @lamoreauxwine in the Finger Lakes! Tried so many beauties but the Red Oak Riesling and 76 Red Blend (Bordeaux Style) had to be among my favs. More on my story and I'm here til Monday if you have any recs!
The Riesling is flowing here in the Finger Lakes ⭐ Story for more!

Did a '20 and '21 Riesling comparison at @hillickandhobbs yesterday. Both beautiful, the '20 was showing juicy and ripe pears and peaches while the '21 led with rocky minerality and elevated acidity.  Can't wait to see what this winery has in store for us! 👏💯👏

My first Finger Lakes trip was a huge success 🥂  Read all about it in my latest blog post, Somm in the Finger Lakes, (link in bio) where I give praise to those with the most stand-out wines for me: @sixeightycellars @lamoreauxwine @forgecellars @atwaterwine @drfrankwine @hillickandhobbs @weisvines @hermannjwiemer and more!

I pour so you can explore! 🍷💕🥂 Now accepting a few new clients in the Hudson Valley and Capital District for staff training and/or educational events. Restaurants, bars, shops: let's up your wine game. Website in bio or DM with Qs!

A superbly crafted, pale pink from @maisonmirabeau 🩷 Notes of white peach, pear, zesty grapefruit and pomelo come across on the nose before carefully refined acidity and a well-balanced finish. I'll be on this all summer 🌞
Summertime splashness

Poppin off the holiday weekend with @champagnehenriot 🍾 Beautifully balanced with notes of apple tart, daffodils and toasted brioche. Pair with your cheese plate, a dozen oysters, dog n fries, the list goes on..
In case you missed my Blind Tasting class at @kinderhookbottleshop last night, you can pick up a bottle in the shop to test your luck any time!

A few of my favorite NZ Sauvignon Blancs from the @dreyfusashby portfolio. @julestaylorwines is full of pink grapefruit and red apple while @thebetterhalfwine has ripe guava, fresh basil and salted lime across the palate. 👏👏
Good times and great wines 🥂 Til next time SoCal!

Just introduced to this sparkling Nebbiolo from @luigi_giordano_winery in Barbera! The 2017 rosé was made in the Champagne method and aged on lees for 9 months! Wilted roses, red raspberries and pine come across on the creamy finish along with fresh herbs and citrus. Got mine at @convivewines in NYC!
Going porchside with this Riesling

Dopff & Irion Crustaces from Alsace is a Sylvaner (80%) and Pinot Blanc (20%) blend. Minerality drives this aperitif style, freshie. Slightly underripe lime and pear are found on the nose before an herbal and floral tinge across the palate. Pair with mussels or cold fish paté! Part of the @dreyfusashby portfolio! @dopffetirion
Sparkling Wines of the World with yours truly! Get your tickets for the 8/17 tasting here: http://bit.ly/3s1xyoe 🍾

social_posts.post_text: Twas a lovely day in Toga 🐎
A few favs from last night's "Sparkling Wines of the World" class. 🍾 Stay tuned for the next one at @parktheaterhudson in a few weeks!
Champagne Mami 🥂 Laherte Freres Extra Brut is comprised of 60% Pinot Meunier and giving notes of pomegranate seeds, rose petals and dried thyme sprigs. $62 on the shelf here at @kinderhookbottleshop

From one of the Loire Valley’s greatest terroirs, Brézé, this Cremant is full of lazer-sharp acid and mossy minerality. 🥂 The blend is about 75% Chenin Blanc and 25% Chardonnay. The tuffeau limestone bedrock comes across on the long finish after notes of ripe green pear, dried persimmon and shaved ginger. Exceptionally done, Arnaud Lambert! Got my bottle from @convivewines in NYC.

Enjoying the always lovely Pierre Peters, one of my favorites from Champagne. I found the bottle on @winechain.co , premier NFT marketplace for rare wines. They work with one of Europe's top sommeliers to source rare and luxury wines, sold on the platform directly from the producers. They use encrypted tokens to prove that every bottle comes directly from the winery and has been stored in ideal conditions!  You can store the bottles in your digital cellar until you're ready to enjoy them. Check it out: winechain.co

A very memorable, 15 yr old premier cru (Vaillon) from Roy-Prevostat & Fils. This ancient (4 century old) estate was originally where monks from Pontigny made their selection to create the Chablis appellation. Still fresh and full of citrus, ripe stone fruit and mouthwatering acidity, we also found notes of honeycomb, gunflint, and walnut shells. Got the bottle at @depwines 👏
Wine with friends 🍷 It's been real, Aspen.. and full of wildlife!

Gamay all day 🍷 This one from Guy Breton's “Cuvée Léa” is perfumed and silky, common for the Chiroubles cru. The organic vineyard is blessed with steep, high-altitude slopes of decomposed granite and a whole mess of old vines. Delicate red berries, white mushrooms, wet leaves and elderflower arise on the nose and across the long finish. $46 for this perfect fall sipper, part of @kermitlynchwine 's portfolio and I got mine at @kinderhookbottleshop

For my fellow acid heads and mineral addicts, meet the Natcool Riesling from @fio.wines
Mosel vineyards within Piesport and Liewen are showing off their slate and loam at the forefront. Daffodils, orange peel and nectarine notes closely follow. Naturally fermented, organically vinified. @skurnikwines distributes, got this one at @kinderhookbottleshop last night.
Fall is for messy hair and sweaters 🍂
Some faves over the Rip

International #sherryweek is November 6-12 and I recommend enjoying any of the @tiopepewines or @gonzalezbyassusa wines, especially paired with a seacuterie board by @conservasdecambados 🐟All my favorite tins and tasting notes on the story now! Thanks @donnawhitewine and @sherrywinesjerez 😘
"My weekend in Montalcino" is on the blog now! Link in bio for the rundown of wineries and restaurants I highly recommend. 😘
All I need for any holiday 🥂 Champagne (@champagnedrappier ) and paté (@talbottandarding )
✨ Sushi and Chenin ✨

From the Pays Nantais (usually home of Muscadet), Loire's western-most region, these Chardonnay vines overlook the Atlantic Ocean. This sea salty wine is fermented with native yeasts in steel and aged only in tank before unfiltered bottling. My notes: quince, spring blossom, green plum, and briney oysters. Made certified organic by @ericchevaliervigneron , part of @kermitlynchwine 's book and available now at @hudsonwinemerchants 🤍
